		<td><b>Re: DefleMask 8</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It makes an unorthodox use of the APU frame counter, and disables interrupts. I actually started a thread talking about that technique here: <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=9296" class="postlink">http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=9296</a><br /><br />The current version of NSFPlay doesn't support it, because it does not implement all features of the frame counter. Several other players are in teh same boat, like NEZPlug++ and VirtuaNSF. NSF players that require the use of interrupts will fail, though surprisingly the PowerPak is okay with it (it doesn't use IRQ).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
